{{third-party|date=January 2018}} {{Infobox writer <!--For more information, see [[:Template:Infobox Writer/doc]].--> | name = Aladino Félix | honorific_prefix = | honorific_suffix = | image = | image_size = | alt = | caption = | native_name = | native_name_lang = | pseudonym = Dino Kraspedon | birth_name = | birth_date = 1905 | birth_place = Pedra do Baú | death_date = 1985 | death_place = | resting_place = | occupation = | language = Portuguese | nationality = Brazilian | ethnicity = | citizenship = | education = | alma_mater = | period = | genre = <!-- or: | genres = --> | subject = Astrophysics | movement = | notableworks = Meu Contato com os discos voadores | spouse = <!-- or: | spouses = --> | partner = <!-- or: | partners = --> | children = | relatives = | awards = | signature = | signature_alt = | years_active = | module = | website = | portaldisp = <!-- "on", "yes", "true", etc; or omit --> }}
'''Aladino Félix''' better known by his [[pen name]] '''Dino Kraspedon''' (1905–2004), was a Brazilian author, right wing paramilitary leader and self-proclaimed messiah of the Jewish people, who claimed in a 1959 book to have been contacted by an extraterrestrial from Jupiter.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=http://www.theguardian.com/world/2018/oct/03/brazil-cult-leader-aliens-terror-aladino-felix-dino-kraspedon|title=Brazil cult leader who 'contacted aliens' backed dictatorship with terror attacks, documents show|last=Phillips|first=Dom|date=2018-10-03|website=the Guardian|language=en|access-date=2018-10-03}}</ref><ref name=reader>{{cite book |last= |first= |authorlink= |coauthors= |title=The New Conspiracy Reader |year=2004 |publisher= |quote=... of the activities of Brazilian contactee/terrorist Dino Kraspedon, the nom de guerre of Aladino Felix, who underwent an alleged contact experience in ... | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=4JHmzr8VYUcC&pg=PA87&dq=Dino+Kraspedon&ei=Ra5dSfi_CIvkywSk7sT-Bw |isbn=0-8065-2542-8 }}</ref><ref name=eccentric>{{cite book |last= |first= |authorlink= |coauthors= |title=Eccentric Lives and Peculiar Notions |year=1999 |publisher= |quote=My Contact with Flying Saucers|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ZzDHPKxDkAwC&pg=PA229&dq=Dino+Kraspedon&ei=NbBdSdHJGZPqyQSauJz-Bw|isbn=0-932813-67-4}}</ref> Much information of a scientific (mainly astrophysics), medical, and moral nature is given in his book.<ref>My Contact with UFO's by Dino Kraspedon</ref>
== Biography ==
Félix was born in Pedra do Baú and is reported to have died in 1985.<ref name=":0" /> Félix served in the army in World War II.<ref name=":0" /> In 1959 Félix under his pen name '''Dino Krespedon''' published ''Meu Contato com os discos voadores'' ([https://books.google.com/books?id=VyKkAAAACAAJ&dq=My+Contact+with+Flying+Saucers My Contact with Flying Saucers]) .<ref name=eccentric/><ref name=mind/> The book tells the story of his claimed contact with a [[flying saucer]] commander, at his home. Félix (as Dino Kraspedon) wrote that he gave the [[extraterrestrial life|extraterrestrial]] visitor was given a lengthy Q&A interview in which the visitor explained advanced concepts in physics and gave insights on how to improve humanity's social conditions on earth. Félix (as Dino Kraspedon), later publicly clarified that he did not witness the male human extraterrestrial leaving or entering any spacecraft.<ref name=reader />
Under his pen name Dino '''Kraspedon''', Félix appeared to correctly predict that there would be a period of terrorism. However Félix seems to have been motivated to fulfill his own prediction since a 2018 Brazilian investigative journalism report revealed that in 1967-68 Félix himself was actually leading a group of 14 police officers in a false flag operation committing acts of terrorism in coordination with a general with close ties to Brazil's right wing dictatorship. The terrorist acts included detonating 14 bombs, stealing arms and explosives and robbing a bank. Evidence shows this terrorism was carried out in order to allow the dictatorship a pretense for tightening their repression of Brazilian society.<ref name=":0" /> Aladino Félix was arrested and charged with terrorism in 1968 and served three years in prison.<ref name="reader" /><ref name="eccentric" /><ref name="mind">{{cite book |last= |first= |authorlink= |coauthors= |title=Turn Off Your Mind |year= |publisher=The Disinformation Company |quote=... as well as a wave of political terrorism in Sao Paulo, the Brazilian Dino Kraspedon, author of My Contact with Flying Saucers (1959), was arrested on ... | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=8jfptmqzTzkC&printsec=frontcover#PPA355,M1 |isbn=0-9713942-3-7 }}</ref><ref name=":0" />
