[[File:The Vision of The Valley of The Dry Bones.jpg|200px|thumb|right|Engraving of "The Vision of The Valley of The Dry Bones" by [[Gustave Doré]] ]]

The '''Vision of the Valley of Dry Bones''' (or The '''Valley of Dry Bones''' or The '''Vision of Dry Bones''') is a [[prophecy]] in [[Ezekiel 37|chapter 37]] of the [[Book of Ezekiel]].<ref>[[Book of Ezekiel]], [http://www.chabad.org/library/bible_cdo/aid/16135 37:1-14]</ref> The chapter details a vision revealed to the prophet [[Ezekiel]], conveying a dream-like [[Reality|realistic]]-[[Naturalism (visual art)|naturalistic]] depiction.

In his vision the prophet sees himself standing in the [[valley]] full of dry human [[bone]]s. He is commanded to carry a prophecy. Before him the bones connect into human figures, then the bones become covered with [[tendon]] tissues, [[flesh]] and [[skin]]. Then God reveals the bones to the prophet as the [[People of Israel]] in [[exile]] and commands the Prophet to carry another prophecy in order to revitalize these human figures, to resurrect them and to bring them to the [[Land of Israel]].

